      <subsection>
        <title>NumPy arrays</title>

        <p>
          NumPy arrays are an efficient way to do computations with a list of numbers. 
          You can also represent vectors or matrices using NumPy arrays. 
          Run the code below to see how it works.
        </p>



        <sage language='python'>
          <input>
            import numpy as np
            X = np.array([1,2,3,4])
            print(X)
            print(2*X)
          </input>
        </sage>

      </subsection>


